sentences: Ehud Asherie (born 1979) is a jazz pianist and organist.
Asherie was born in Israel in 1979.
He moved with his family to Italy at the age of three, where he attended the Sir James Henderson School, now The British School of Milan, and then to the United States when he was nine.
Asherie played Hammond organ on his 2010 quartet release, Organic.
He recorded his first solo piano album, Welcome to New York, in 2010.
An asterisk (*) indicates that the year is that of release.
